Articles.Content:
I just started modelling, and I seem to have a good handle on things, but apparently not as much as I thought. I've been looking at guides on these forums as well as YouTube videos, and none quite yet explain my issue. I'm trying to make a simple box as a structural part just to learn the process of getting stuff into the game. I can get as far as creating the .mu, and my node definitions in my .cfg have integers where needed (as it's a slightly modified version of the stock Modular Girder Segment), but the part doesn't show up at all in-game, and the log states that the model doesn't exist. I'm not sure if it's something in Blender(v2.78a) or Unity(v5.4.0p4) that I'm missing.

Edited March 5, 2017 by SchwinnTropius
added .cfg; changed title to [solved]

Using a MODEL node requires a directory path.

Quote

    MODEL
    {
        model = BasicBoxTopLevel/BasicBoxSubLevel/BasicBox
        scale = 1,1,1
    }

  • GameData
    • BasicBoxTopLevel
      • BasicBoxSubLevel

 

So if your model is only one folder deep:

Quote

    MODEL
    {
        model = BasicBoxTopLevel/BasicBox
        scale = 1,1,1
    }

I'm not 100% positive the scale is necessary but I always include it.

Alternatively you can just use the mesh line if you only have the one model in the directory.

Quote

mesh = BasicBox.mu
